# PRD: Zero-Friction UX Audit and Fix

## Objective
Walk every user flow end-to-end, identify friction, fix it. Goal: zero friction, maximum clarity.

## Wave 1 (Parallel): Auth + Engagement List + Engagement Create
- [ ] 1A: Auth flows (login/logout/forgot password)
- [ ] 1B: Engagement list (tabs/search/sort/filters)
- [ ] 1C: Engagement create form (all dropdowns populated)

## Wave 2 (Parallel): Engagement Detail + Clients + Stage Transitions
- [ ] 2A: Engagement detail all tabs, wire all buttons
- [ ] 2B: Client list + create + detail + edit + add user
- [ ] 2C: Stage transitions (button, confirm, API call, refresh)

## Wave 3 (Parallel): RFI + Review + Files/Messages/Checklists
- [ ] 3A: RFI list + create + detail + questions (add/edit/delete)
- [ ] 3B: Review list + create + detail + collaborators + export PDF
- [ ] 3C: File upload + message send + checklist operations

## Wave 4 (Parallel): Settings + Admin + Search
- [ ] 4A: User management (list/create/edit)
- [ ] 4B: Team management (list/create/edit/members)
- [ ] 4C: Settings pages + global search

## Wave 5 (Parallel): End-to-End Verification
- [ ] 5A: Complete engagement lifecycle
- [ ] 5B: Complete review lifecycle
- [ ] 5C: Final screenshot audit of every page
